name: none

description:
Sanford obtained the Molecule Man's wand after if was given to him by the Thing after he determined it was non-functional. Sanford decides to pretend to be the Molecule Man with his friends Cynthia (Iron Girl) and Boyd. Despite the wand's supposed non functional status it is activated and when Cynthia touches it she is transformed from a child into a fully grown woman. She has the Molecule Man's facial markings and a personality that is a mix between her own and the Molecule Man.

Cynthia goes back into town and turns her mother into a doll. Iron Man shows up, and the Molecule Man/Cynthia fight him, then leave. Later, they clash again. Cynthia drops the wand and returns to normal. Iron Man eventually gets the wand, and Reece almost takes him over, before the Man-Thing takes it away. Since the Man-Thing has no mind, the Molecule Man can't possess it.
name: More or Less... The Return of the Molecule Man!
Assault On Armor City Part 3: Destroy; Annual Report; Cold Fire; Mrs. A. Takes A Holiday; Five Minutes

deck: First appearance of the Face Thief
description: Tony helps the Masters of Silence in defeating the newly released Face Thief.
name: The Fury of the Face Thief!

description:
Overview

In a nutshell this is a story arc about the haunting origin of Daredevil, aka Matt Murdock, why he became a lawyer, and the tragedy of his first true love.

As a young boy, Matt Murdock gained enhanced senses in an accident that also robbed him of his sight. But when his father was gunned down in cold blood, Murdock used his strange gifts to get justice as the costumed hero, Daredevil! Every comic book fan knows this story... or do we? Now it's time to flesh out the early days of the Man Without Fear!
name: The Championship Season

description:
Overview

Rocked by the events of last issue, Matt Murdock sets out for vengeance! But will he learn that justice and revenge are not one and the same? Plus: Matt meets the most beautiful girl in the world!
name: The Measure of a Man

description:
Overview

The new firm of Nelson and Murdock needs clients, so howzabout the Fantastic Four? Meanwhile, the early days of DD's career continue as the Man Without Fear follows the trail to his father's killers! Plus: a classic enemy makes his first move!
name: Stepping into the Ring

first_appearance_locations.name: Law Offices of Nelson and Murdock

location_credits.name: Law Offices of Nelson and Murdock

description:
Overview

Continuing the new look at Daredevil's early days by the award-winning team of Jeph Loeb and Tim Sale! Life is pretty good for New York's newest super hero. That is, until he crosses paths with his first super-villain: Electro! Then, the final fate of Jack Murdock's killers changes Matt's life forever! All this... and Karen Page gets kidnapped? Who knew the early days of the Man Without Fear were anything like this?
name: Never Lead With Your Left

description:
Overview

The Owl kidnapped to Karen Page, Daredevil rescued her, and Foggy watched something destroyed his heart.
name: Against the Ropes

description:
Overview

Matt Murdock is down for the count! And the Purple Man wants... Karen Page?! In the thrilling climax by the award-winning team of Jeph Loeb and Tim Sale, the Man Without Fear must make peace with his past so he can live with his future!
name: The Final Bell

first_appearance_locations.name: Law Offices of Nelson and Murdock

location_credits.name: Law Offices of Nelson and Murdock

description: A new ongoing series explores the new Gotham City from a mysterious vantage point. Plus, the first of a series of BATMAN: BLACK AND WHITE backup stories by a variety of creators, beginning with writer Warren Ellis and artist Jim Lee. Frequent "No Man's Land" writer Devin Grayson (THE TITANS, Black Widow) is joined by her "Fear of Faith" collaborator Dale Eaglesham and inker John Floyd for a thrilling new series that explores Batman and the people who help him in his fight. Told through the eyes of an unknown party, the series offers a new perspective on the Dark Knight Detective. Each extra-sized issue will feature 8-page BATMAN: BLACK AND WHITE-style stories by an array of writers and artists, beginning with an installment courtesy of writer Warren Ellis (TRANSMETROPOLITAN, PLANETARY) and artist Jim Lee (DIVINE RIGHT: THE ADVENTURES OF MAX FARADAY, FLINCH). In the guest-star-packed BATMAN: GOTHAM KNIGHTS #1 (featuring a cover by Dave Johnson), a horrifying crime attracts Batman's attention and forces him to revisit the ghosts of his past as Oracle, Nightwing and Robin attempt to help him solve the mystery.
name: Constants; To Become the Bat

description: Batgirl guest-stars in an issue that also features a black-and-white backup story written and drawn by John Byrne and the debut of regular cover artist Brian Bolland (BATMAN: THE KILLING JOKE)! Batman and Batgirl fight to save a group of kidnapped Gothamites from being sold overseas as slave labor, but Batgirl's personal struggle with her killer instincts may prove to be the death of not only her, but everyone else.
name: Down With the Ship; With Robin, the Boy Wonder

description: Part 1 of a 2-part story introducing a new villain: Samsara. It's a horrifying night for the Batman when a shooting is just the beginning of a killing spree in Gotham, as the bizarre spirit named Samsara begins inhabiting the bodies of everyone Batman fails to save.
name: Samsara Part One of Two: Bad Karma; Broken Nose

description: In the conclusion of a 2-part story, Samsara's origin is revealed as Batman struggles to solve the mystery of his increasingly dangerous pursuer! In order to defeat his new foe, the Dark Knight must confront his own limitations as well as the youthful vengeance fantasies that have shaped the course of his life.
name: Samsara Part Two of Two: Letting Go; Greetings from Gotham City

description: The Key has entered Gotham City, and his goal is to send Batman over the edge by removing the Dark Knight's moral code aginst taking life. As Batman fights for control of his soul, Batgirl and Azrael struggle to keep the Dark Knight from making the biggest mistake of his life.
name: Locked; Hide and Seek

description: It's a great day for Gotham's fences when a large section of the Gotham Bank and Trust's vault of safety-deposit boxes previously thought lost in the quake resurfaces and is quickly looted. Initially willing to leave the case to the GCPD, the Dark Knight agrees to look into it after being begged by a distraught Oracle. What could have been taken from the box belonging to the former Batgirl that is causing such distress? Don't miss this amazing revelation about Oracle's past!
name: Personal Effects; The Riddle

description: Badly wounded, Batman struggles to help a hundred innocent citizens victimized by a bomb. Battling overwhelming odds, he is reminded of incidents from his past immediately after the death of his parents.
name: Oblation

description:
Part 1 of the 4-part "Transference," guest-starring Catwoman!

Catwoman's nighttime encounter with Batman and a Catwoman imposter turns out to be one of the strangest nights of the Feline Fatale's life, with nothing being what it seems...especially the Dark Knight's behavior.

Plus a black & white back-up story by Brian Azzarello and Eduardo Risso.

Notes:

  • Ranked #68 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".
name: Transference, Part 1 of Four

concept_credits.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

first_appearance_concepts.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

description:
Part 2 of the 4-part "Transference," guest-starring Nightwing and Robin!  
 
Trapped in the WayneCorp buliding, Batman engages in a psychological war with a stronger, smarter-than-ever Hugo Strange, but the aftermath of this battle will be a nightmare from which Nightwing, Robin, and the rest of Batman's associates may never recover.
name: Transference, Part 2 of Four; Blackout

description:
Part 3 of the 4-part "Transference," guest-starring Nightwing and Robin!

Batman...dead? That's what it looks like after his confrontation with Hugo Strange. As Nightwing tries to figure out if he's still alive, Robin discovers Batman's personal logs about each of them, which only leads to more questions.

In the back up, BATMAN BLACK & WHITE Year One tale, "Guardian," the original Green Lantern, Alan Scott, checks up on Gotham's new protector to ensure that the city is in safe hands.
name: Transference, Part 3 of Four; Guardian

description:
"Transference" concludes! Bruce Wayne has been kidnapped by Hugo Strange, which leaves his rescue up to Nightwing and Robin! Can they save their mentor from this madman, or will the Batman's secret finally be revealed?

Hugo Strange escapes from Nightwing and Robin before they and Alfred go to collect Bruce Wayne who has turned up after the fire at Wayne Enterprises. However, when they get Wayne alone, it is quite clear that he doesn't remember being Batman, and finds the existence of the Batcave quite disturbing. When Robin and Nightwing try to rendezvous with Catwoman, she shoots at them; they allow themselves to be captured by her, and find themselves in the lair of Hugo Strange - Catwoman is actually his assistant Dora. Strange has also kidnapped Bruce Wayne, and tries to force the heroes to admit that Wayne is Batman. Neither Nightwing nor Robin will admit this, and Wayne truly appears to be a scared, ineffectual rich guy, even when their lives are in danger. By this point, Strange is totally confused - he killed Batman, but Wayne didn't die; he runs away deliriously. Later, when they get back to the Manor, Nightwing recites an oath which snaps Wayne out of a post-hypnotic state and reminds him of his true nature. He also explains that the files on his computer are his own. Elsewhere, Strange is admitted to an asylum, still raving that he is Batman.
name: Transference, Part 4 of Four; Snow Job!

description: A team-up between Barbara Gordon and...Alfred?! When wheelchair-bound Gothamities find themselves the victims of a string of muggings, Oracle makes it her goal to bring the culprit down.
name: Damages; The Black and White Bandit

description:
The not-to-be-missed conclusion to "Officer Down!" James Gordon faces his final destiny and Batman must accept the possibility of the loss of a valued comrade, and a life which never will be quite the same. Plus, a black-and-white backup feature written by Harlan Ellison and illustrated by Gene Ha.

It's been over two weeks since James Gordon was shot by Jordan Rich, and the man responsible has walked away scot-free and is suing the city for wrongful arrest. Gordon is slowly on the mend, but has nevertheless made the decision to retire from the police force - a decision that saddens the major crimes unit and angers Bullock. Mike Akins is to take over permanently as Commissioner, with Bock receiving the promotion to Chief of Police. Detective Montoya blames herself for what happened - she and Allen had the opportunity to get Rich convicted and let the opportunity slip through their fingers.

On the roof of the GCPD building, Gordon introduces Batman to the new Commissioner. Batman does not take the news of Gordon's retirement well. The next day, Montoya calls in sick...and Bullock gets a bad feeling about it. His feeling is deserved, as Montoya makes her way determinedly to Rich's apartment. She bursts in, gun in hand, willing Rich to attack her so that she can kill him in self-defence. However, Bullock arrives and talks her out of wasting her career on a nothing like Jordan Rich, reminding her of what Gordon told them the night he was shot...that a police officer's greatest power is to deprive someone of freedom, not of life.

That night, Batman and Gordon meet at Gordon's house, coming to an understanding about what has happened. Their working relationship is over, but the two men will remain friends. Elsewhere, Jordan Rich's apartment is empty, with splashes of what looks suspiciously like blood on the floor. Unaware of this, Bullock and Montoya meet in Kelly's Plough. She complains that there is no justice, but is consoled by Bullock.
name: Officer Down Part Seven: The End; Funny Money

description: The deadly twins known as Double Dare have stolen some jewels from the Penguin, and just about everyone is looking to retrieve the property--along with the heads of the thieves on a platter!
name: Sibling Rivalry; The Bet

description:
Poison Ivy escapes Arkham Asylum and heads for a ""Save the Rainforest"" benefit--where she decides to take a few hostages. Hostages that include Robin's father, Jack Drake!

When Poison Ivy learns that a Rain Forest Fund Raiser is being held in Gotham City, she breaks out of Arkham Asylum. Bruce Wayne, meanwhile, meets Jack and Dana Drake (parents of Tim Drake) at the Gotham City Rain Forest Fundraiser. Jack and Dana are sharing a cell phone call with Tim when Poison Ivy crashes the fund raiser.

Ivy describes how outrageously backward the party is since the products used at the fundraiser represent the killing of trees. Ivy orders her plants into action and takes hostages.

Tim Drake hears what is happening at the fundraiser, changes into his alter ego, Robin, and rushes to the scene. Robin negotiates with Ivy about her problem with uncaring industrialists who make contracts for Rain Forest deforestation while attending that fundraiser. Ivy decides not to use her toxins on Robin, giving Batman time to overpower Ivy.
name: Far From the Tree; Stormy Nether

description: "Matatoa" part 1! Batman must face a seemingly immortal madman named Matatoa who seeks to take the life of an undefeated warrior--and Batman's the only one Matatoa has heard tales of.
name: Matatoa, Part 1 of 2; The Bat No More...?

description: "Matatoa" part 2! Batman battles for his life with the eternal shaman whose destiny includes killing the Dark Knight and taking on his nocturnal crime-fighting duties! It would secure Batman a safe, crime-free Gotham City for all eternity--but at what cost does it all truly come?
name: Matatoa, Part 2 of 2; A Moment in the Light

description: Aquaman guest-stars! As the Dark Knight realizes that he's become more of a loner since the loss of Gordon, Alfred's leave of absence and Oracle's anger with him, Batman finds odd comfort in the company of the King of the Seas.
name: Cavernous; Fat City

description: What's it like to be a small-time hood in Gotham City, with the spectre of the Batman haunting every street corner, alleyway and rooftop in the city? Follow a mook named Titus as his truck-jacking scheme is unhinged by "The Factor of Fear".
name: The Factor of Fear!; The Call

description: "Retribution" part 1. Bruce Wayne makes a trip to Metropolis for a meeting with the new CEO of LexCorp and has a run-in with Superman. Meanwhile, Dick Grayson and Batman both have to deal with the possibility that all of Grayson's family isn't dead after all, when his grandfather comes to town!
name: Retribution Part 1 of 2: Sons and Lovers; The Lesson

description: In "Retribution" part 2, a man named Yoska has emerged from Dick Grayson's past, claiming to be Dick's grandfather! Where Yoska has come from and why assassins are on his tail are answers that Batman and Nightwing must figure out quickly if they're going to keep this final link to Dick's past alive!
name: Retribution Part 2 of 2: Contested

description: With the Joker's crazed super-villains terrorizing the DCU, Batman and Spoiler are left to defend Gotham City from a truly twisted new threat, as the Joker's brand of chemical warfare has transformed the creatures of Gotham. Plus, a Batman Black & White backup "The Bottom Line," written by Michael Golden and illustrated by Jason Pearson!
name: Bugged Out

description: The weight of the world on Batman's shoulders plus the weight of the world on Bruce Wayne's shoulders may be too much for one man to bear, especially one under the effects of the Scarecrow's fear-causing chemicals. Plus, a Batman black-and-white short illustrated by Darwyn Cooke!
name: Fear of Success; Here Be Monsters

description: A DC FULL COVERAGE! entry-point issue! Batman's life has been rough of late, but now it's Bruce Wayne's world that's thrown on its ear. Both Batman's and Bruce Wayne's inner circles become smaller and smaller. And why would Bruce Wayne be buying a handgun? Plus, a Batman Black & White backup, "Urban Legend," by the Tellos team of writer Todd Dezago (IMPULSE) and penciller Mike Wieringo (ADVENTURES OF SUPERMAN), with inker Karl Story (BATMAN).
name: The Devil You Know; Urban Legend

description: "Bruce Wayne: Murderer?" Part 10! As Bruce Wayne languishes in prison on a brutal murder charge, his closest allies try and come to terms with the horrific reality of the situation. Only...not everyone who loves him thinks he's completely innocent. Plus, a Batman Black & White backup, "Bruce Wayne is Batman!," written by Cyrus Voris & Chris Bachalo, with art by Bachalo (STEAMPUNK).
name: Innocent Until

description: A fugitive from justice and his own comrades, Batman brutally punishes the criminal element of Gotham City, and is surprised when he's paid an unwanted visit from the Man of Steel. Meanwhile, Alfred searches for more clues to the murder that's been pinned on Bruce Wayne. Plus, a Batman Black & White backup, "Never Say Die," written by Dwayne McDuffie with art by Denys Cowan.
name: Murder? Positive I.D.

description: "Bruce Wayne: Fugitive" Part 7! Enter...the Mortician! In all of Batman's war against crime, he's never come across a more ghoulish adversary. Back at Wayne Manor, Robin makes an important discovery that questions his opinion regarding Bruce's guilt. Plus, a Batman Black & White backup, "Thin Edge of a Dime," written by Don McGregor (Zorro, Black Panther) with art by Dick Giordano (BATMAN: HOLLYWOOD KNIGHT).
name: The Mortician, Part 1: Anti-Hero

description: Part 2 of a tale featuring the deadly Mortician! Batman must devise a way to stop the Mortician from raising more homicidal zombies, while battling the army he's already brought back to life! Plus, a Batman Black & White backup, "No Escape," written by Paul Kupperberg with art by John Watkiss.
name: The Mortician, Part 2: Zombie Zero

description: What's eating Azrael? And why is he using those closest to Batman as punching bags? Join us for the first part of a story where the Agent of the Bat plans to take over Batman's cowl…permanently! This story concludes in AZRAEL: AGENT OF THE BAT #91. Plus, a Batman Black & White backup, "Punchline," written by Doug Alexander with art by Rob Haynes (Daredevil: Ninja).
name: Turnabout, Part 1

description: Ultimate Hulk makes his way through New York city, smashing everything in his way. Spider-man does his best to try and stop him. Spider-man gets himself into a tight spot(no pun intended). Hulk grabs him by the head.
name: Spider-Man & Hulk Part One of Two

description: Originally, this story was supposed to be only one issue, but there's just too much action to contain! Our all-new Web-Spinner attempts to lure the most powerful creature alive away from the heart of New York City, without getting smashed! And as the U.S. Army closes in, will Spider-Man learn that he and the jade giant are somehow connected?
name: Spider-Man & Hulk Part Two of Two

description: Suave millionaire Tony Stark, head of his cutting edge company Stark Industries, possesses the unique Irontech technology, from which springs his greatest achievement: the armored assault suit codenamed Iron Man! And despite how carefully Stark guards his invention, a certain maniacal Latverian dictator is determined to have it! To ensure that it is his, the monstrous monarch sends his deadly Mandroids to enforce his will! And that's when Stark's young admirer, Peter Parker, shows up at Stark Industries... and it all hits the fan!
name: Spider-Man & Iron Man Part One of Two

description: Sent by a hostile power to steal Stark's advanced technology, the Mandroids appear to have succeeded — that is, unless our young web-spinner can save the day! But what chance does our flesh-and-blood hero have against an army of armored assassins? And why is Iron Man powerless against them?
name: Spider-Man & Iron Man Part Two of Two

description: What if there was a man incarcerated in Ryker's Island whose all-consuming obsession was the total elimination of the criminal element by any means necessary? And what if he escaped? Well, there is and he has! Now, the former police officer and current vigilante named Frank Castle prowls the streets, gunning down the Underworld! And if a certain young web-slinger gets in his way... well, there's a bullet with Spider-Man's name on it, too!
name: Spider-Man & The Punisher

description: Last issue the one-man-army named Frank Castle escaped from prison and began his mission to wipe out the men responsible for the death of his family! Now one of the guilty party seeks legal protection from attorney Matt Murdock. But it may only be Murdock's alter ego, the vigilante named Daredevil, who can save his client from the Punisher's wrath, but then again, maybe not! And guess who's caught in the middle? That's right, our young wall-crawling Spider-Man!
name: Spider-Man & The Punisher & Daredevil Part One of Two

description: One by one, the evil men that slaughtered Frank Castle's family are being knocked off. Only one guilty guy remains, and lawyer Matt Murdock has sworn to make him pay through the courts! But it'll take more than police protection to save him from the Punisher, it'll take the combined power of two of the city's most mysterious masked vigilantes: Daredevil, the Man Without Fear, and the wall-crawling Spider-Man! It's a rumble in the (urban) jungle as three of Marvel's most popular characters collide!
name: Spider-Man & The Punisher & Daredevil Part Two of Two

description:
Peter Parker goes to visit the Baxter Building, HQ of the Fantastic Four.

It will be involved in a Skrull invasion that will began a big fight into the "Marvel Comics new offices"!

This plot is really a big joke created by Bendis and Mahfood and it's not part of the Ultimate Universe Storyline.

In fact the Ultimate version of the Fantastic Four team is younger and not so famous as the original group.

Special appearance of Joe Quesada, Ralph Macchio and Mahfood!
name: Spider-Man & The Fantastic Four

description: Despondent that the funding for his cherished limb regeneration research is to be, pardon the pun, cut off, biologist Curt Conners turns himself into a guinea pig, and finds himself transformed into the lethal Lizard! The rapacious reptile seeks refuge in the dank recesses of the New York City sewer system, pursued by our fledgling web-spinner! But unknown to them both, something far more mysterious lurks in the subterranean shadows, something known as the macabre Man-Thing!
name: Spider-Man & The Man-Thing
